    "Autopoietic process involves the integration of external irritations in which every participating system observe other but responds throughout its own codes and mode of functioning.",
    "Therefore, constant selfreferential regeneration of the systems produces the phenomena of scientific authorship which we know today.",
    "It is historically evident that authorship in that regard is not stable concept-isolated to one aspect like individual or science (throughout the ethical standards alone).",
    "Scientific authorship is a relational phenomenon which is always lesser then its parts (each and every system involved in the creation) but cannot be reduced to either one of it.",
    "What we propose is to have that in mind when considering authorship in the relationship with the new technologies like generative AI, LLM's."
